Portrait of a Lady on Fire

France, 1770. Marianne, a painter, is commissioned to do the wedding portrait of Héloïse, a young woman who has just left the convent. 
Héloïse is a reluctant bride to be and Marianne must paint her without her knowing. 
She observes her by day, to paint her secretly.


This is my 2nd emtional movie:
Brokeback Mountain is a 2005 American Neo-Western romantic drama film directed by Ang Lee and produced by Diana Ossana and James Schamus. 
Adapted from the 1997 short story of the same name by Annie Proulx, the screenplay was written by Ossana and Larry McMurtry. 
The film stars Heath Ledger, Jake Gyllenhaal, Anne Hathaway, and Michelle Williams and depicts the complex emotional and sexual relationship 
between two American cowboys named Ennis Del Mar and Jack Twist in the American West from 1963 to 1983.
